{"slug":"intro-chains","graph":"both","title":"Three hops to anyone","sub":"the three cheapest intro routes to each prospect, major lab, and funder","headline":"Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google DeepMind sit <strong>three hops</strong> from AoC — and since the 2026-07 edge audit, all 24 best routes open rival-free through AIUC.","prose":{"intro":"<p>The map shows who is adjacent to whom; this panel turns that into asks. For eight company targets — the top prospects, the major labs, and one VC — plus the top five funders, we compute the three cheapest intro routes each, then count who keeps showing up in the middle. The recurring middlemen are the relationships worth investing in.</p>","how":"<p>The route-finder works like a maps app asked for alternates: the best path, then the next-best that differs somewhere, never revisiting a stop. Each hop has a price. A business tie costs 1, a shared investor 2, a rival 10 — so a route through one competitor wins only if it saves ten partner hops. Three routes per target means two backups when a relationship goes cold. On the funding side, routes start from the 3 grantees nearest AoC (Gray Swan AI, Apollo Research, Haize Labs), and every hop counts the same. One structural fact: every person in the funding graph has exactly one edge, so no route passes <em>through</em> a person — a chain can only end at one. That is why the person routes end with a name and a role.</p>","method":"<p>Yen (1971) k-shortest loopless paths, k=3, via networkx <code>shortest_simple_paths</code> (Dijkstra subroutine on the weighted company graph; unweighted BFS hops on the funding graph). Edge weights business=1, shared-investor=2, competitor=10 are design choices, not measurements — reweighting reorders routes but cannot create reachability. For the 7 company pairs with two edge types we keep the cheaper. Targets were curated at bake time from the competitor-nominations and funder-shortlist panels plus the four majors; all 8 company targets sit inside AoC's 182-node component (0 unreachable), while 2 of 5 shortlist funders (Sequoia Capital, Insight Partners) have no funding-graph path from any AoC-linked grantee. Funding caveats: 85/199 edges lack a year, and affiliation edges carry roles but no dollars.</p>"},"caveat":"AoC's seat is still mostly rivalry — 4 of its 5 edges are competitor ties. But the fifth, an unverified business tie to AIUC, stopped being a dead end in the 2026-07 edge audit: AIUC's certification ties (ElevenLabs, Intercom's Fin, UiPath) give AoC a rival-free corridor reaching 149 companies. That corridor hangs on a single unverified edge; every other route still starts through a rival.","inputs":{"companies":{"nodes":188,"edges":530},"funding":{"nodes":200,"edges":199}},"data":{"companyChains":[{"target":{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"},"why":"top nominated prospect","chains":[{"score":2,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":5,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"intercom-fin","label":"Intercom (Fin)","graph":"companies"},{"id":"anthropic","label":"Anthropic","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":5,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"anthropic","label":"Anthropic","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]}]},{"target":{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"},"why":"top nominated prospect","chains":[{"score":4,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":4,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"gray-swan-ai","label":"Gray Swan AI","graph":"companies"},{"id":"google-deepmind","label":"Google DeepMind","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true}]},{"score":5,"nodes":[{"id":"agents-of-chaos","label":"Agents of Chaos","graph":"companies"},{"id":"aiuc","label":"AIUC","graph":"companies"},{"id":"uipath","label":"UiPath","graph":"companies"},{"id":"microsoft","label":"Microsoft","graph":"companies"},{"id":"protect-ai-palo-alto-networks","label":"Protect AI (Palo Alto Networks)","graph":"companies"},{"id":"servicenow","label":"ServiceNow","graph":"companies"}],"edges":[{"label":"business","verified":false},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified":true},{"label":"business","verified"